> The key to perfection with this classic dish is how thinly you can slice your steak. For wafer thin ribbons put your steak in the freezer for one hour, then while it is still solid (but not totally frozen) slice it micro-thin. By getting it nice and cold you'll find it infinitely easier to cut thin slices for a tender finish!

Slice the @flank steak{1} into thin ribbons (a few millimetres thick if your knife skills are up to the task). Roughly chop the @closed cup mushrooms{2}(halved), peel and finely dice the @onion{1}(finely diced) and separate the @broccoli{1} into florets. Bring a large, high-sided #pot{} of water to the boil on the hob for your pasta.

In a #bowl{}, thoroughly coat the steak strips in the @cornflour{2%tbsp}, @paprika{1%tsp} and a good pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Put @olive oil{2%tsp} in a #non-stick pan{} on high heat. Brown off your steak in batches for about ~{45%seconds} on each side (in small batches to stop it stewing). Once cooked, put your steak on a #plate{} to the side. 

> It should still have a hint of pink in the middle.

Turn the heat down to medium and add in @olive oil{1%tbsp} along with the onions. Cook them gently for ~{5%minutes} to soften them up (don't brown them off though). Finally, add the mushrooms.

Add your @wheat tagliatelle{440%g} into the boiling water with @salt{½%tsp}. After ~{3%minutes}, add the broccoli into the same #pot{} (on top of the pasta but submerged). The broccoli should be cooked after ~{3-4%minutes}, at which point your pasta will be ready too.

Once the mushrooms have cooked (which should take a few mins), turn the heat to low. Add in all of the steak together with @beef stock pot{½}, the @tomato puree{1%tbsp}, @water{5%tbsp}, the @sour cream{1%container} and @lemon juice{1%tsp}. Add the @Worcestershire sauce{1%tsp} and cook for a few mins to thicken up. Add @?sugar{½%tsp} if you have some.

Drain the pasta and broccoli as soon as they are ready.

> You'll need to separate the broccoli from the pasta but you'll have saved on washing up!

Finally, serve the stroganoff onto the tagliatelle with the broccoli on the side.